        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 8 at 8:19PM EDT until July 8 at 8:30PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 819 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles northwest of
Sedley, or 9 miles north of Courtland, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and powerlines.

This severe storm will be near...
Ivor around 835 PM EDT.
Zuni around 845 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include
Vicksville, Booth Fork, Pons, Berlin, Bethel Church, Lumberton, Ellis
Fork, Manry, Delk Crossroads, and Indika.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
